# Example boundary condition file (.bci)
# Format: <x> <y> <type> <value>
# Types: HVAR = time-varying water level, QVAR = time-varying discharge
# Values: filename containing time series data

# West boundary - inflow hydrograph
100 100 QVAR inflow_hydrograph.txt

# East boundary - free boundary
300 100 FREE

# Stage monitoring point
150 150 GAUGE gauge1.txt